    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Chinese University of Hong Kong</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis: A high cardiovascular risk is present in subjects with pre-diabetes in Hong Kong
      Chinese.

      The investigators plan to assess Chinese subjects in Hong Kong who have pre-diabetes
      (impaired fasting glucose, IFG; or impaired glucose tolerance, IGT) based on oral glucose
      tolerance test (OGTT) on their cardiovascular risk status such as obesity, hypertension and
      lipid profile.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
